WHOLESALE MARKET-BASED RATE TARIFF OF LOCKHART POWER COMPANY
Availability: Lockhart Power Company (Lockhart) makes electric energy and capacity available under this FERC electric tariff to any purchaser, except as prohibited below. Lockhart also makes available, to any purchaser, except as prohibited below, the ancillary services listed below. Ancillary Services: PJM: Lockhart offers regulation and frequency response service, energy imbalance service, and operating reserve service (which includes spinning, 10-minute, and 30-minute reserves) for sale into the market administered by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") and, where the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff permits, the self-supply of these services to purchasers for a bilateral sale that is used to satisfy the ancillary services requirements of the PJM Office of Interconnection. Third Party Provider: Third-party ancillary services: Regulation Service, Energy Imbalance Service, Spinning Reserves, and Supplemental Reserves. Sales will not include the following: (1) sales to an RTO or an ISO (i.e., where the entity has no ability to self-supply ancillary services but instead depends on third parties); (2) sales to a traditional, franchised public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier, or sales where the underlying transmission service is on the system of the public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier; and (3) sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers. Applicability: This tariff is applicable to all wholesale sales of energy, capacity, ancillary services, firm transmission rights by Lockhart at market-based rates. Rates: All sales shall be made at rates established by agreement between the purchaser and Lockhart. Other Terms and Conditions: All other terms and conditions shall be established by agreement between Lockhart and the purchaser. Revisions to the Tariff: Lockhart may file revisions to this Tariff by notifying purchaser in writing and by unilaterally making the appropriate filing with the Commission pursuant to the provisions of Section 205 of the Federal Power Act; provided, however, that such revision shall not affect the rates, terms and conditions of transactions entered into prior to the date of such revision, unless otherwise agreed by the parties. Compliance with Commission Regulations: Lockhart shall comply with the provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning Lockhart's market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes Lockhart to engage in affiliate sales under this tariff or otherwise restricts or limits Lockhart's market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning Lockhart's market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this Tariff. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority: Lockhart has not been found to have any limitations on its market-based rate authority in a particular region. Lockhart has received the following waivers and authorizations: (1) waiver of the filing requirements of Subparts B and C of Part 35 of the Commission's regulations, except Sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15, and 35.16; (2) waiver of the accounting, reporting, and other requirements of Parts 41, 101 and 141 of the Commission's regulations, except Sections 141.14 and 141.15; and (3) blanket authorization for future issuances of securities or assumptions of liabilities pursuant to Section 204 of the FPA, 16 U.S.C. 824c, and Part 34 of the Commission's regulations. See Lockhart Power Co., Letter Order, Docket No. ER07-1137-000 (Aug. 6, 2007). Seller Category: Lockhart is a Category 1 seller in all regions, as defined in 18 C.F.R. 35.36(a). Effective Date: This tariff is effective on the date specified by the Commission.
